text:

Show HN: Garden grows and cultivates collections of Git trees
text:
Garden is a unique tool that I've been tinkering on for a bit and figured it was worth sharing.

Garden is a unix-y powertool that mashes together shell scripting, a flexible and simple variable expression mini-language and multi-repo environment variable management into a simple command-line tool.

Garden is an improvement over a big pile o' repos and personal shell scripts. If you find yourself tinkering with random repos and writing one-off while scripts for building random projects then you just might find garden useful as a way to automate, record and share your workflows.

Have fun!

Ask HN: How to make the most out of an educational business trip?
text:
My manager asked me if I would like to go on a cross-country educational business trip. I told him it would be a great opportunity to learn. The team I would be visiting is much more experienced than we are, and I am also relatively new to the field so this is really a dream come true in terms of professional development.

However, this all comes with a bit of pressure. I would like to make the most out of this experience. I will only be there for a few weeks, so I want to learn as much as possible during that time. That means I need to hit the ground running and ask the right questions and do the right things. How can I make the most out of this trip?
